  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NDB Loan Package</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project involves providing a loan of US$ 24 Mn to NDB, for on-lending to their SME business.  National Development Bank PLC (NDB) is a listed Sri Lankan bank, which was established via a merger of the National Development Bank of Sri Lanka (NDBSL) and its commercial banking subsidiary, NDB Bank Limited (NBL), in August 2005. NDB provides a broad range of financial products and services, including project finance, Bancassurance, housing finance, investment banking and stock-broking services via subsidiaries and associate companies.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Three decades of conflict in the past had limited the Sri Lankan government&apos;&apos;s capacity to support the SME sector and thereby to allocate crucial resources to boost lagging incomes. The proposed project will help in addressing this constraint by funding the Bank&apos;&apos;s operations/expansion and promoting financial inclusion by means of financing of SMEs.  The proposed project would facilitate private sector development via access to credit for growing SMEs in Sri Lanka. Given the importance of SMEs in Sri Lanka, the cascading effect of this finance would go a long way in creating employment, reducing poverty and stimulating the economy.</narrative>
  </description>
